logical continuation and no less flexible than White's last move.} ({We
already know that} 4... g6 5. d4 exd4 6. Nxd4 Bg7 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. Nc3 {is
pleasant for White.}) (4... Nf6 $2 {runs into} 5. Ng5 $16) 5. d4 {Occupying
the centre is equally unpromising as one move earlier.} ({The natural} 5. d3 {
runs into} Na5 {, immediately yielding Black a good position.} 6. Re1 (6. Bb5+
c6 7. Ba4 b5 8. Bb3 Nf6 9. Nbd2 O-O 10. Re1 {Mohammad,M (2281) -Abdulla,A 
(2464) Dhaka 2021 (½-½, 53)} Nxb3 11. axb3 a5 12. Nf1 c5 $15 {Zaksaite,S 
